Implemented support for reviver in parse. Handle underflow.
Fixed context of revive and replace callbacks
Parse all numbers as LosslessNumber again. LosslessNumber accepts any type of value now. Renamed `transform` to `revive` again and handle LosslessNumbers correctly when reviving.
Fixed code coloring of a code block
Try out buble (works right out of the box...)
Drop node 4 from travis config (babel doesn't support node 4)
Add node 4 again in travis, it works but slow
Fixed #4: parser not handling strings equaling a JSON delimiter like `"["` correctly
Also test node.js v9 on travis-ci
